article.headline: Wagner 82, Quinnipiac 70
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Joey Mundweiler hit a 3-pointer to force overtime, then hit two more in the extra session to lead Wagner to an 82-70 win over Quinnipiac on Monday. All five starters finished in double figures for Wagner (17-6, 10-2 NEC), led by Mundweiler's 19 points. Mark Porter had 18 and Jamal Smith added 17. Casey Cosgrove had 16 points and Bryan Geffen added 15 to lead Quinnipiac (12-11, 8-4). Mundweiler's tied the game at 62 with 19 seconds to play. The Skyhawks had four shots on their final possession, but Cosgrove missed a runner in the lane with 2 seconds left. Wagner scored the first five points of the overtime and never trailed again. Quinnipiac played the game without leading scorer DeMario Anderson, who missed the game for personal reasons. Anderson is second in the NEC in scoring, averaging 20.9 points per game.
